      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "OUR ULTIMATE HEIDI (4) has had more than seven weeks off since the Bathurst Gold Tiara series where she placed in her heat then came from the back row for a midfield finish in the consolation. Kept up to the mark with a trial and could measure up. There was merit in the debut performance of REBECCA RHAYNE BOW (5) when beaten only 4.5m into fourth at this circuit and distance. Similar draw and is open to natural improvement. SHAKE (1) produced a much better effort at start number two when she scored by nearly 12 metres at Redcliffe. This is stronger but she is likely to get the favours from the inside draw. GO MINNIE (6) had a back row draw last start but was runner-up both times she started on this line. WANNABE WICKED (3) could progress after coming from this barrier for second on debut here last week.",
